"Y" Align="Yes"><Para TopMargin="5" LeftMargin="0" FirstLineIndent="2" Bold="Yes"><B>81.</B> Section 121 of the Act is amended by adding âandâ at the end of paragraph (<I>d</I>) and by repealing paragraph (<I>e</I>).</Para></Block><Block LineCnt="Y" Align="Yes"><Para TopMargin="5" LeftMargin="0" FirstLineIndent="2" Bold="Yes"><B>82.</B> (1) The definition â<AltLang xml:lang="fr">date dâabandon du forage</AltLang>â in subsection 122(1) of the French version of the Act is repealed.</Para></Block><Block LineCnt="Y" Align="Yes"><Para TopMargin="5" LeftMargin="0" FirstLineIndent="2" Bold="Yes">(2) The definition âwell termination dateâ in subsection 122(1) of the English version of the Act is replaced by the following:</Para></Block><Block LineCnt="Y" Align="Yes"><MarginalNote>âwell termination dateâ<br />Â« <I>date dâabandon du puits</I> Â»<br /></MarginalNote><Para TopMargin="5" LeftMargin="0">âwell termination dateâ means the date on which a well has been abandoned, completed or suspended in accordance with any applicable regulations respecting the drilling for petroleum made under Part III.</Para></Block><Block LineCnt="Y" Align="Yes"><Para TopMargin="5" LeftMargin="0" FirstLineIndent="2" Bold="Yes">(3) Subsection 122(1) of the French version of the Act is amended by adding the following in alphabetical order:</Para></Block><Block LineCnt="Y" Align="Yes"><MarginalNote>Â« date dâabandon du puits Â»<br />â<I>well termination date</I>â<br /></MarginalNote><Para TopMargin="5" LeftMargin="0"><AltLang xml:lang="fr">Â« date dâabandon du puits Â» Date Ã  laquelle le puits a Ã©tÃ© abandonnÃ© ou complÃ©tÃ© ou son exploitation suspendue conformÃ©ment aux rÃ¨glements applicables en matiÃ¨re de forage pris sous le rÃ©gime de la partie III.</AltLang></Para></Block><Block LineCnt="Y" Align="Yes"><Para TopMargin="5" LeftMargin="0" FirstLineIndent="2" Bold="Yes">(4) Subsection 122(2) of the French version of the Act is replaced by the following:</Para>